summary: Donna Vekic has made history at Wimbledon 2024 by reaching her first Grand Slam semifinal. Despite Sun's impressive run, Vekic prevailed in a gripping rally to secure her spot in the semis. This victory marks a significant milestone for Vekic, who has previously reached the quarterfinals of a Grand Slam 42 times before. Vekic's opponent in the semifinals will be Jasmine Paolini, who also had a successful quarterfinal match against Emma Navarro. Experts and tennis enthusiasts eagerly await this thrilling matchup, as both Vekic and Paolini aim to advance to the final at the prestigious All England Club.

name: Modi Putin
summary: Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India made his first official visit to Russia since the start of the conflict in Ukraine, highlighting the continuing strong ties between the two nations. Despite concerns over the war, Modi and Russian President Vladimir Putin emphasized their "bonds of friendship." The meeting focused on arms discussions, with India seeking to balance its relationship with Russia while also navigating international pressure. While some observers criticized Modi's embrace of Putin amid the ongoing conflict, Russia pledged to release Indian nationals who had been misled into joining its military. Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy expressed disappointment over the meeting, while experts suggest that it underscores the difficulties of isolating Russia and highlights the complex diplomatic challenges faced by India.

The tour, titled "Something To Give Each Other," promises to bring Sivan's captivating stage presence and sultry vocals to his fans down under. name: The Devil Wears Prada sequel
summary: A highly anticipated sequel to the iconic 2006 film "The Devil Wears Prada" is reportedly in development at Disney, with screenwriter Aline Brosh McKenna, who penned the original screenplay, in negotiations to return. The sequel will reportedly focus on Emily Blunt's character, Emily Charlton, and is said to involve the return of Anne Hathaway as Andy Sachs and Meryl Streep as the formidable Miranda Priestly. The project has been met with excitement from fans and industry insiders alike, with many eager to see the continuation of the beloved fashion industry satire.

name: Longlegs
summary: Nicolas Cage plays a serial killer in the new horror movie 'Longlegs', directed by Oz Perkins. The film has also been praised for its "mesmerizing" performances by Maika Monroe and Nicolas Cage, and its "satanic power" (Hollywood Reporter). One reviewer even calls it this summer's "great 'anti-blockbuster'" (BBC.com).

name: Jillian Segal
summary: In response to rising concerns, Australia has taken significant steps to combat anti-Semitism. The government has appointed Jillian Segal as the country's first Special Envoy for Combatting Antisemitism. This move has been met with praise from Jewish Australians, who have expressed a desire to feel safe and free from discrimination. While recognizing that criticism of Israel is not always anti-Semitic, the Attorney General has emphasized the need to distinguish between legitimate criticism and hateful rhetoric. The appointment of a special envoy demonstrates Australia's commitment to eradicating anti-Semitism and fostering a more inclusive society for all.

name: Death Valley
summary: Extreme heat is gripping the United States, with Death Valley experiencing scorching temperatures that could break a world record. Temperatures in the valley are forecast to reach 130 degrees Fahrenheit (54.4 degrees Celsius) this weekend, threatening to surpass the current record of 134 degrees Fahrenheit (56.7 degrees Celsius) set in 1913. The heat wave has already taken a deadly toll, with a motorcyclist dying from heat exposure in the area. Despite the dangerous conditions, tourists continue to flock to Death Valley, seeking to experience the unique environment and natural beauty. While temperatures are not as extreme in other parts of the country, the heat wave is still causing widespread discomfort and health risks for millions of people.
